hpicfDhcpv4ServerMIB.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerMIB

revisions.description: The initial version of this MIB module

hpicfDhcpv4ServerMIB.contactinfo: Hewlett-Packard Company 8000 Foothills Blvd. Roseville, CA 95747
hpicfDhcpv4ServerMIB.description: This MIB module is for entities implementing the server side of the Bootstrap Protocol (BOOTP) and the Dynamic Host Configuration protocol (DHCP) for Internet Protocol version 4(IPv4).

InetAddressIPv4.name: InetAddressIPv4
InetAddressIPv4.description: Represents an IPv4 network address: octets contents encoding 1-4 IPv4 address network-byte order The corresponding InetAddressType value is ipv4(1). This textual convention SHOULD NOT be used directly in object definitions since it restricts addresses to a specific format. However, if it is used, it MAY be used either on its own or in conjunction with InetAddressType as a pair.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerEnable.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerEnable
hpicfDhcpv4ServerEnable.description: Global configuration to enable or disable DHCPv4 server on the device. The 'disableWithClearConfig' enum disables DHCPv4 Server along with removing all the DHCPv4 Server related configuration.

hpicfDhcpv4PingPktNumber.name: hpicfDhcpv4PingPktNumber
hpicfDhcpv4PingPktNumber.description: This object specifies the number of ping packets sent by DHCP server to an IP address before assigning this address to a requesting client.

hpicfDhcpv4PingTimeOut.name: hpicfDhcpv4PingTimeOut
hpicfDhcpv4PingTimeOut.description: This object specifies the amount of time the DHCPv4 server must wait before timing out a ping packet.

hpicfDhcpv4ClearStatistics.name: hpicfDhcpv4ClearStatistics
hpicfDhcpv4ClearStatistics.description: All the DHCPv4 server and BOOTP statistics will be cleared when this object is set to 'true'. An SNMP 'get' on this object will always return 'false'.

hpicfDhcpv4ClearBindings.name: hpicfDhcpv4ClearBindings
hpicfDhcpv4ClearBindings.description: When the IP address of this object is set to 0.0.0.0, all IP bindings will be cleared. Specific IP binding will be cleared when IP address is provided. An SNMP 'get' on this object will always return 0.0.0.0 .

hpicfDhcpv4ClearConflictIP.name: hpicfDhcpv4ClearConflictIP
hpicfDhcpv4ClearConflictIP.description: When the value of this object is set to 0.0.0.0, all conflicts will be cleared. Specific IP conflict will be cleared when IP address is provided. An SNMP 'get' on this object will always return 0.0.0.0 .

hpicfDhcpv4ConflictsLog.name: hpicfDhcpv4ConflictsLog
hpicfDhcpv4ConflictsLog.description: Global configuration to enable or disable DHCPv4 server conflicting address logging.

hpicfDhcpv4TrapEnable.name: hpicfDhcpv4TrapEnable
hpicfDhcpv4TrapEnable.description: This object will enables or disables the DHCPv4 server traps.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerVlanEnable.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerVlanEnable
hpicfDhcpv4ServerVlanEnable.description: Specifies the VLANs on which DHCPv4 server is enabled.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerOperStatus.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerOperStatus
hpicfDhcpv4ServerOperStatus.description: Specifies operational status of DHCPv4 protocol.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerDBFile.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerDBFile
hpicfDhcpv4ServerDBFile.description: A location to store the lease database, to retrieve it after a reboot. The location must be given in the form of a URL as defined in RFC 2396. The allowed character sets and the encoding rules defined in RFC 2396 section 2 apply.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerDBWriteDelay.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerDBWriteDelay
hpicfDhcpv4ServerDBWriteDelay.description: The number of seconds to delay writing the DHCP lease database file after a database change. This potentially allows grouping multiple database changes into a single write. The default is 300 seconds.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerDBWriteTimeout.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerDBWriteTimeout
hpicfDhcpv4ServerDBWriteTimeout.description: The number of seconds to wait for the database file transfer to finish before giving up and declaring a failure. A value of 0 means continue retrying indefinitely.

hpicfDhcpServerDBFileWriteAttempts.name: hpicfDhcpServerDBFileWriteAttempts
hpicfDhcpServerDBFileWriteAttempts.description: Number of attempts that have been made to write the DHCP lease database to a configured file location.

hpicfDhcpServerDBFileWriteFailures.name: hpicfDhcpServerDBFileWriteFailures
hpicfDhcpServerDBFileWriteFailures.description: Number of times that an attempt to write the DHCP lease database to a configured file location has failed.

hpicfDhcpServerDBFileReadStatus.name: hpicfDhcpServerDBFileReadStatus
hpicfDhcpServerDBFileReadStatus.description: This object indicates whether we were able to successfully load the DHCP lease database from the configured location after the last reboot.

hpicfDhcpServerDBFileWriteStatus.name: hpicfDhcpServerDBFileWriteStatus
hpicfDhcpServerDBFileWriteStatus.description: This object indicates whether the DHCP lease database is currently synchronized with the configured file server. 'notConfigured' means that we have not been configured with a server location. 'delaying' means that we are waiting for the write delay to expire before writing the current database. 'inProgress' means that a lease database transfer is active. 'succeeded' means that all leases in our database have been written to the server. 'failed' means that the last attempt to write our lease database failed.

hpicfDhcpServerDBFileLastWriteTime.name: hpicfDhcpServerDBFileLastWriteTime
hpicfDhcpServerDBFileLastWriteTime.description: The time that we last successfully wrote our lease database to the server. This object will contain a value of all zeroes if we have not written our lease database since the last reboot.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerDBFTPort.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerDBFTPort
hpicfDhcpv4ServerDBFTPort.description: A location to store the port value of the FT Server. The default port value will be 69 for TFTP and 22 for SFTP

hpicfDhcpv4ServerDBSFTPUsername.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerDBSFTPUsername
hpicfDhcpv4ServerDBSFTPUsername.description: A location to store the Username of the SFTP Server. The default value of username is root.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerDBSFTPPassword.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerDBSFTPPassword
hpicfDhcpv4ServerDBSFTPPassword.description: A location to store the Password of the SFTP Server.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerDBValidateSFTPServer.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerDBValidateSFTPServer
hpicfDhcpv4ServerDBValidateSFTPServer.description: This object sets the validate-sftp-server flag. When enabled, the user must login to the SFTP server to verify and accept the public key of the server. When disabled, the public key is accepted automatically.

hpicfBootpCountRequests.name: hpicfBootpCountRequests
hpicfBootpCountRequests.description: The number of packets received that contain a message type of 1 (BOOTREQUEST) in the first octet and do not contain option number 53 (DHCP Message Type) in the options.

hpicfBootpCountReplies.name: hpicfBootpCountReplies
hpicfBootpCountReplies.description: The number of packets sent that contain a message type of 2 (BOOTREPLY) in the first octet and do not contain option number 53 (DHCP Message Type) in the options.

hpicfDhcpv4CountDiscovers.name: hpicfDhcpv4CountDiscovers
hpicfDhcpv4CountDiscovers.description: The number of DHCPDISCOVER (option 53 with value 1) packets received.

hpicfDhcpv4CountOffers.name: hpicfDhcpv4CountOffers
hpicfDhcpv4CountOffers.description: The number of DHCPOFFER (option 53 with value 2) packets sent.

hpicfDhcpv4CountRequests.name: hpicfDhcpv4CountRequests
hpicfDhcpv4CountRequests.description: The number of DHCPREQUEST (option 53 with value 3) packets received.

hpicfDhcpv4CountDeclines.name: hpicfDhcpv4CountDeclines
hpicfDhcpv4CountDeclines.description: The number of DHCPDECLINE (option 53 with value 4) packets received.

hpicfDhcpv4CountAcks.name: hpicfDhcpv4CountAcks
hpicfDhcpv4CountAcks.description: The number of DHCPACK (option 53 with value 5) packets sent.

hpicfDhcpv4CountNaks.name: hpicfDhcpv4CountNaks
hpicfDhcpv4CountNaks.description: The number of DHCPNACK (option 53 with value 6) packets sent.

hpicfDhcpv4CountReleases.name: hpicfDhcpv4CountReleases
hpicfDhcpv4CountReleases.description: The number of DHCPRELEASE (option 53 with value 7) packets received.

hpicfDhcpv4CountInforms.name: hpicfDhcpv4CountInforms
hpicfDhcpv4CountInforms.description: The number of DHCPINFORM (option 53 with value 8) packets received.

hpicfDhcpv4CountPools.name: hpicfDhcpv4CountPools
hpicfDhcpv4CountPools.description: The number of DHCP server IP pools.

hpicfDhcpv4CountAutoBindings.name: hpicfDhcpv4CountAutoBindings
hpicfDhcpv4CountAutoBindings.description: The number of DHCP server dynamic bindings.

hpicfDhcpv4CountStaticBindings.name: hpicfDhcpv4CountStaticBindings
hpicfDhcpv4CountStaticBindings.description: The number of DHCP server manual bindings.

hpicfDhcpv4CountExpiredOrFreeBindings.name: hpicfDhcpv4CountExpiredOrFreeBindings
hpicfDhcpv4CountExpiredOrFreeBindings.description: The number of DHCP server lease bindings that have expired or free.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolTable.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolTable
hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolTable.description: Table that contains objects for DHCPv4 server pool information.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolEntry.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolEntry
hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolEntry.description: A set of objects that are used to support DHCPv4 server pool information.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolName.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolName
hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolName.description: The name of this pool entry.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolNetworkAddress.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolNetworkAddress
hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolNetworkAddress.description: The network address of this DHCP pool entry.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolNetworkAddressMask.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolNetworkAddressMask
hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolNetworkAddressMask.description: The network address mask of this DHCP pool entry.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolDomainName.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolDomainName
hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolDomainName.description: The domain name for the client if the server allocates the address for the client from this pool.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolNetBIOSNodeType.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolNetBIOSNodeType
hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolNetBIOSNodeType.description: The NetBIOS node type for a Microsoft DHCP client.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolLeaseTime.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolLeaseTime
hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolLeaseTime.description: The number of seconds remaining until this DHCP lease times out. A value of 0xffffffff indicates an infinite lease.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolBootFile.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolBootFile
hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolBootFile.description: The name of the file that is used as a boot image.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolLowThreshold.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolLowThreshold
hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolLowThreshold.description: The low threshold for available free addresses in this pool. If the value for available free addresses in this pool becomes equal to or less than this value, a dhcpv4ServerFreeAddressLow event is generated for this pool. No more dhcpv4ServerFreeAddressLow events will be generated for this subnet during this execution of the DHCP server until the value for available free addresses has exceeded the value of hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolHighThreshold.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolHighThreshold.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolHighThreshold
hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolHighThreshold.description: The high threshold for available free addresses in this pool. If a dhcpv4ServerFreeAddressLow event was generated for this pool, and the value for available free addresses has exceeded the value of hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolHighThreshold, then a hpicfDhcpv4ServerFreeAddressHigh event will be generated. No more hpicfDhcpv4ServerFreeAddressHigh events will be generated for this pool during this execution of the DHCP server until the value for available free addresses becomes equal to or less than the value of hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolLowThreshold.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolFreeAddresses.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolFreeAddresses
hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolFreeAddresses.description: The number of IPv4 addresses which are available within this pool.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerDNSServerAddress.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerDNSServerAddress
hpicfDhcpv4ServerDNSServerAddress.description: The IP address of DNS IP servers that are available to a DHCP client. One IP address is required and supports up to eight IP addresses. Each IP address is separated by a comma and the list is terminated by a semicolon.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerNetBIOSNameServer.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerNetBIOSNameServer
hpicfDhcpv4ServerNetBIOSNameServer.description: The NetBIOS WINS servers that are available to a DHCP client. One IP address is required and supports up to eight IP addresses. Each IP address is separated by a comma and the list is terminated by a semicolon.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerDefaultRouter.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerDefaultRouter
hpicfDhcpv4ServerDefaultRouter.description: The default routers that are available to a DHCP client. One IP address is required and supports up to eight IP addresses. Each IP address is separated by a comma and the list is terminated by a semicolon.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerTFTPServerName.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerTFTPServerName
hpicfDhcpv4ServerTFTPServerName.description: The TFTP server name of this DHCP pool entry.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerTFTPServerIpAddress.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerTFTPServerIpAddress
hpicfDhcpv4ServerTFTPServerIpAddress.description: The TFTP server IP address of this DHCP pool entry.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerStaticIpAddress.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerStaticIpAddress
hpicfDhcpv4ServerStaticIpAddress.description: The manual IP address of this DHCP pool entry.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerStaticIpAddressMask.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerStaticIpAddressMask
hpicfDhcpv4ServerStaticIpAddressMask.description: The manual IP address mask of this DHCP pool entry.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerStaticHardwareAddress.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerStaticHardwareAddress
hpicfDhcpv4ServerStaticHardwareAddress.description: The ethernet MAC address of a client.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolIsAuthoritative.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolIsAuthoritative
hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolIsAuthoritative.description: This object indicates whether this DHCP server is the sole authority for the IP subnet configured in this pool. When configured as authoriative, the server will actively respond with DHCP ACK or NACK appropriately for all the received DHCP REQUEST and INFORM packets from the clients belonging to this subnet. DHCP INFORM packets received from the clients on a non-authoritative pool will always be ignored.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerRangeTable.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerRangeTable
hpicfDhcpv4ServerRangeTable.description: Table that contains objects for the range of IP addresses in the pool.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerRangeEntry.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerRangeEntry
hpicfDhcpv4ServerRangeEntry.description: A set of objects that are used to support pool IP range.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerRangeStartAddress.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerRangeStartAddress
hpicfDhcpv4ServerRangeStartAddress.description: The start address of the range. The value of hpicfDhcpv4ServerRangeStartAddress must be less than or equal to the value of hpicfDhcpv4ServerRangeEndAddress and should be within the pool subnet.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerRangeEndAddress.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerRangeEndAddress
hpicfDhcpv4ServerRangeEndAddress.description: The last address in the range. The value of hpicfDhcpv4ServerRangeEndAddress must be greater than or equal to the value of hpicfDhcpv4ServerRangeStartAddress and should be within the pool subnet.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolOptionTable.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolOptionTable
hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolOptionTable.description: Table that contains objects for DHCPv4 Server options.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolOptionEntry.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolOptionEntry
hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolOptionEntry.description: A set of objects that are used to support DHCPv4 server options.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolOptionCode.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolOptionCode
hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolOptionCode.description: The DHCP option code as per RFC 2132.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolOptionType.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolOptionType
hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolOptionType.description: This specifies the type of pool option data.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolOptionData.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolOptionData
hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolOptionData.description: This specifies data in dotted hexadecimal or ASCII character string or IP addresses format based on hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolOptionType value. Each byte in hexadecimal character strings is two hexadecimal digits. Each byte can be separated by a period, colon, or white space. ASCII strings that contain white spaces must be enclosed within quotation marks. One IP address is required and supports up to eight IP addresses. Each IP address is separated by a comma and the list is terminated by a semicolon.

hpicfDhcpv4BindingTable.name: hpicfDhcpv4BindingTable
hpicfDhcpv4BindingTable.description: Table that contains objects for DHCPv4 server dynamic lease bindings.

hpicfDhcpv4BindingEntry.name: hpicfDhcpv4BindingEntry
hpicfDhcpv4BindingEntry.description: A set of objects that are used to support DHCPv4 server dynamic lease bindings.

hpicfDhcpv4BindingIpAddress.name: hpicfDhcpv4BindingIpAddress
hpicfDhcpv4BindingIpAddress.description: The IP address assigned to a specific client.

hpicfDhcpv4BindingHardwareAddress.name: hpicfDhcpv4BindingHardwareAddress
hpicfDhcpv4BindingHardwareAddress.description: The ethernet MAC address of a client.

hpicfDhcpv4BindingLifeTime.name: hpicfDhcpv4BindingLifeTime
hpicfDhcpv4BindingLifeTime.description: The life time of the binding entry in seconds. A value of 0xffffffff indicates an infinite life time.

hpicfDhcpv4ConflictIPTable.name: hpicfDhcpv4ConflictIPTable
hpicfDhcpv4ConflictIPTable.description: Table that contains objects for DHCPv4 server address conflicts.

hpicfDhcpv4ConflictIPEntry.name: hpicfDhcpv4ConflictIPEntry
hpicfDhcpv4ConflictIPEntry.description: A set of objects that are used to support DHCPv4 server conflicting address (use of the same IP address by two hosts) entry.

hpicfDhcpv4ConflictIPAddress.name: hpicfDhcpv4ConflictIPAddress
hpicfDhcpv4ConflictIPAddress.description: IP address which is duplicated and used by two hosts.

hpicfDhcpv4ConflictIPDetectionMethod.name: hpicfDhcpv4ConflictIPDetectionMethod
hpicfDhcpv4ConflictIPDetectionMethod.description: The server detects conflicts using ping. The client detects conflicts using gratuitous Address Resolution Protocol (ARP).

hpicfDhcpv4ConflictIPDetectionTime.name: hpicfDhcpv4ConflictIPDetectionTime
hpicfDhcpv4ConflictIPDetectionTime.description: The system time at which a DHCP address conflict happens. If there has been no change since the last re-initialization of the local system, this object contains the date and time of local system initialization. If there has been no change since the entity was added to the local system, this object contains the date and time of the insertion.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerNotifyDuplicateIpAddr.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerNotifyDuplicateIpAddr
hpicfDhcpv4ServerNotifyDuplicateIpAddr.description: The IPv4 address found to be a duplicate. Duplicates are detected by servers, which issue an ICMP ECHOREQUEST prior to offering an IPv4 address lease, or by a client issuing a gratuitous ARP message and reported through a DHCPDECLINE message.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerNotifyDuplicateMac.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerNotifyDuplicateMac
hpicfDhcpv4ServerNotifyDuplicateMac.description: The offending MAC address which caused a duplicate IPv4 address to be detected, if captured by the server, else 00-00-00-00-00-00.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerNotifyClientOrServerDet.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerNotifyClientOrServerDetected
hpicfDhcpv4ServerNotifyClientOrServerDet.description: Duplicate IPv4 addresses can be detected either by a server, using an ICMP ECHO message, or by a client using ARP. This object is set by the server to (1) if the client used DHCPDECLINE to mark the offered address as in use, or to (2) if the server discovered the address in use by some client before offering it.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerClientPhysicalAddress.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerClientPhysicalAddress
hpicfDhcpv4ServerClientPhysicalAddress.description: The hardware address of the client that requested the IP lease.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerFreeAddressLow.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerFreeAddressLow
hpicfDhcpv4ServerFreeAddressLow.description: This notification signifies that the number of available IPv4 addresses for a particular shared network has fallen below the value of hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolLowThreshold for that shared network.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerFreeAddressHigh.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerFreeAddressHigh
hpicfDhcpv4ServerFreeAddressHigh.description: This notification signifies that the number of available IPv4 addresses for a particular shared network has risen above the value of hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolHighThreshold for that shared network.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerDuplicateAddress.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerDuplicateAddress
hpicfDhcpv4ServerDuplicateAddress.description: This notification signifies that a duplicate IPv4 address has been detected. The DHCP server can detect this condition through the ping-before-offer mechanism. Alternatively, the client may have sent a DHCPDECLINE back to the server; this is assumed to be the result of the client detecting that the address was in use. In either case, the DHCP server marks the IPv4 address as unavailable for leasing to clients. The hpicfDhcpv4ServerNotifyClientOrServerDetected object indicates whether the client or server detected this condition.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerIfLeaseLimitExceeded.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerIfLeaseLimitExceeded
hpicfDhcpv4ServerIfLeaseLimitExceeded.description: This notification indicates that there are no more IP leases available to offer on the receiving interface.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerCompliance.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerCompliance
hpicfDhcpv4ServerCompliance.description: The compliance statement for HP routing switches that support DHCP server.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerCompliance1.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerCompliance1
hpicfDhcpv4ServerCompliance1.description: The compliance statement for HP routing switches that support DHCP server.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerCompliance2.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerCompliance2
hpicfDhcpv4ServerCompliance2.description: The compliance statement for HP routing switches that support DHCP server.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerBaseGroup.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerBaseGroup
hpicfDhcpv4ServerBaseGroup.description: Controls the global configuration of the DHCPv4 server.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerLeaseDataBaseGroup.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerLeaseDataBaseGroup
hpicfDhcpv4ServerLeaseDataBaseGroup.description: Group of objects to support lease database parameters.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerBootpCountersGroup.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerBootpCountersGroup
hpicfDhcpv4ServerBootpCountersGroup.description: Group of objects that count various BOOTP events.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerCounterGroup.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerCounterGroup
hpicfDhcpv4ServerCounterGroup.description: Group of objects that count various DHCPv4 events.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolGroup.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolGroup
hpicfDhcpv4ServerPoolGroup.description: Group of objects to support DHCPv4 server pool parameters.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerRangeGroup.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerRangeGroup
hpicfDhcpv4ServerRangeGroup.description: Group of objects to support DHCPv4 server IP range parameters.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerOptionGroup.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerOptionGroup
hpicfDhcpv4ServerOptionGroup.description: Group of objects to support DHCPv4 server raw option parameters.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerBindingGroup.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerBindingGroup
hpicfDhcpv4ServerBindingGroup.description: Group of objects to support DHCPv4 server dynamic binding parameters.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerConflictGroup.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerConflictGroup
hpicfDhcpv4ServerConflictGroup.description: Group of objects to support DHCPv4 server conflict parameters.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerNotifyObjectsGroup.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerNotifyObjectsGroup
hpicfDhcpv4ServerNotifyObjectsGroup.description: Group of objects required for notifications.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerLeaseDataBaseGroup1.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerLeaseDataBaseGroup1
hpicfDhcpv4ServerLeaseDataBaseGroup1.description: Group of objects to support lease database parameters.

hpicfDhcpv4ServerBaseGroup1.name: hpicfDhcpv4ServerBaseGroup1
hpicfDhcpv4ServerBaseGroup1.description: Controls the global configuration of the DHCPv4 server.
